The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Downpour turns fatal for dozen

 OUR BUREAU

 June 17: Farmers tilling their land, children playing outside their homes and women cooking in their kitchen lightning strikes turned lethal for many as rain and thunderstorms lashed south Bengal today.

 The toll was nearly a dozen, including a nine-year-old. Rakibul Islam was struck by lightning when he was playing on a field near his home in Barasats Ganjee Mill area.

 Nadia was the worst-hit with six persons killed by lightning and one buried under his hut after it collapsed.

 Amirul Mondal, 30, a resident of Habibpur in Nadias Ranaghat, about 60 km from Calcutta, was playing football around 10 this morning when he was struck by lightning. He died on the spot. 

 Three of his friends who were playing with him were admitted to hospital with burn injuries. 

 In Mathpara, also in Ranaghat, lightning killed Nemai Biswas, 34, while he was tilling his land. 

 Farmers Sahidul Mondal, 40, from Dhantola, Idbar Malita, 24, from Nabadwip and Nasiruddin Mandol, 30, from Krishnagunj met the same fate when they were at work.

 At Kaligunj, about 150 km from Calcutta, Mono Mandol, 22, a grocer, was returning home at around 11 last night when he was struck by lightning and killed.

 Death came to Altab Sheikh, 35, while he was sitting at home. His mud hut in Nadias Nakashipara, about 130 km from Calcutta, collapsed on him this morning.

 Nadia district magistrate Onkar Singh Meena said all the bodies have been sent for post-mortem. I have ordered an immediate inquiry to arrive at the compensation for the dead, he said. 

 In Burdwan district, three persons were killed by lightning in the Kalna and Katwa subdivisions, about 165 km from Calcutta. 

 In Karui village of Katwa, farmer Sheikh Salim, 30, died when he went out to the field. 

 Swapna Mondal, a 34-year-old farm labourer, was also struck by lightning while at work in Basirhat in North 24 Parganas.

 Rekha Rani Ghosh, 50, and her daughter, Annapurna Ghosh, 23, were in the kitchen when a bolt of lightning struck their tin roof. The residents of Kalnas Bhaturia village died immediately.




